    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mancala is a generic name for a family of two-player turn-based strategy board games played with small stones, beans, or seeds and rows of holes or pits in the earth, a board or other playing surface. The objective is usually to capture all or some set of the opponent's pieces.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
